    <section name="Introduction">
      <subsection name="What is Gallery Magick Image Processing?">
        <p>
          Gallery Image Processing basically provides an image file processing library,
          using <a href="http://www.graphicsmagick.org/">GraphicsMagick</a>
          or <a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/">ImageMagick</a> to manipulate image files.
        </p>
        <p>
          Gallery Image Processing aims to provide the following:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="core/index.html"><strong>Gallery Image Processing Core Library</strong> </a> :
            programmatic Utilities to process image files.
            <em>(Note: available since 1.0.0)</em>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="cms-plugins/index.html"><strong>Gallery Image Processing CMS Plugins</strong></a> :
            Hippo CMS Plugins such as a Custom Gallery Processor using
            <strong>Gallery Image Processing Library Core</strong>
            <em>(Note: not available yet)</em>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
    </section>

    <section name="Project status">
      <p>
        Please see <a href="release-notes.html">Release Notes</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        See the
        <a href="http://forge.onehippo.org/gf/project/gallery-magick">forge project page</a>
        for more info about the project itself.
      </p>
    </section>
